  "text": "# ArangoDB Authentication and Authorization Audit\n\n## Overview\n\nThe ArangoDB authentication and authorization infrastructure is implemented across multiple components in the C++ codebase. The system manages user credentials, validates JWT tokens, and enforces access control at the database and collection levels.\n\n## 1. User Authentication and Management\n\n**File:** `arangod/Auth/UserManager.h` and `arangod/Auth/UserManagerImpl.h`/`cpp`\n\n**Key Classes and Functions:**\n- `UserManager` (interface in `arangod/Auth/UserManager.h`): Abstract base class defining the user management interface with methods for:\n  - `storeUser()`: Add or update users\n  - `removeUser()`: Delete users\n  - `userExists()`: Check user existence\n  - `checkCredentials()`: Validate username/token pairs\n  - `databaseAuthLevel()`: Get user's database access level\n  - `collectionAuthLevel()`: Get user's collection access level\n  - `enumerateUsers()`: Iterate through all users\n  - `createAccessToken()`/`accessTokens()`/`deleteAccessToken()`: Manage API tokens\n\n- `UserManagerImpl` (in `arangod/Auth/UserManagerImpl.h`/`cpp`): Concrete implementation that:\n  - Manages user cache from `_system/_users` collection\n  - Implements permission level resolution\n  - Handles user creation and initialization (including root user via `createRootUser()`)\n  - Manages database and collection-level permissions\n\n## 2. JWT Token Validation for REST API\n\n**File:** `arangod/Auth/TokenCache.h` and `arangod/Auth/TokenCache.cpp`\n\n**Key Classes and Functions:**\n- `TokenCache`: Caches authentication tokens (both Basic and JWT) with methods:\n  - `checkAuthentication()`: Validates incoming authentication (HTTP Basic or JWT)\n  - `validateJwtBody()`: Extracts and validates JWT payload\n  - `validateJwtHeader()`: Validates JWT header format\n  - `validateJwtHMAC256Signature()`: Validates HMAC-SHA256 signed tokens\n  - `validateJwtES256Signature()`: Validates ES256 (ECDSA) signed tokens\n  - `checkAuthenticationJWT()`: Main JWT validation entry point\n  - `setJwtSecrets()`: Update active and passive JWT signing secrets\n\n- `TokenCache::Entry`: Result structure containing:\n  - Username\n  - Authentication status\n  - Token expiry time\n  - JWT roles and token string\n  - Allowed paths\n\n## 3. Authorization Context\n\n**File:** `arangod/Utils/ExecContext.h` and `arangod/Utils/ExecContext.cpp`\n\n**Key Classes and Functions:**\n- `ExecContext`: Carries execution context information including:\n  - Current user identity\n  - Current database context\n  - System-level auth level (`_systemDbAuthLevel`)\n  - Database-level auth level (`_databaseAuthLevel`)\n  - Admin user flag (`_isAdminUser`)\n  - User roles and JWT token\n  - Key methods:\n    - `current()`: Get current thread's execution context\n    - `superuser()`: Get internal superuser context\n    - `isAdminUser()`: Check if user has admin privileges\n    - `isSuperuser()`: Check if context is superuser\n    - `isInternal()`: Check if context is internal operation\n\n- `ExecContextScope`: RAII guard for temporarily switching execution context\n- `ExecContextSuperuserScope`: Temporary superuser context elevation\n\n## 4. User Management REST Endpoint (/_api/user)\n\n**File:** `arangod/RestHandler/RestUsersHandler.h` and `arangod/RestHandler/RestUsersHandler.cpp`\n\n**Key Classes and Functions:**\n- `RestUsersHandler`: Handles REST requests for user management:\n  - `getRequest()`: GET /_api/user/* - list users and their permissions\n  - `postRequest()`: POST /_api/user/* - create users or set passwords\n  - `putRequest()`: PUT /_api/user/* - update user permissions\n  - `patchRequest()`: PATCH /_api/user/* - partial updates\n  - `deleteRequest()`: DELETE /_api/user/* - delete users\n  - `generateUserResult()`: Format user response\n  - `generateDatabaseResult()`: Format database permission response\n\n## 5. Default Authentication Settings\n\n**Files:** `arangod/GeneralServer/AuthenticationFeature.h`/`cpp` and `arangod/GeneralServer/AuthenticationOptions.h`\n\n**Key Classes and Functions:**\n- `AuthenticationFeature`: Singleton managing server-wide authentication with:\n  - `collectOptions()`: Defines command-line options for authentication\n  - `validateOptions()`: Validates configuration\n  - `prepare()` and `start()`: Initialize authentication subsystem\n  - `loadJwtSecretsFromFile()`/`loadJwtSecretFolder()`: Load JWT signing keys\n  - `jwtSecrets()`: Get active and passive JWT secrets\n  - `userManager()`: Access the UserManager singleton\n  - `tokenCache()`: Access the TokenCache singleton\n\n- `AuthenticationOptions` struct with default values:\n  - `active = true`: Authentication enabled by default\n  - `authenticationUnixSockets = true`: Require auth on Unix sockets\n  - `authenticationSystemOnly = true`: Only system-level auth by default\n  - `authenticationTimeout = 0.0`: No timeout for token cache (indefinite)\n  - `sessionTimeout = 3600.0`: 1 hour session timeout for web interface JWT\n  - `minimalJwtExpiryTime = 10.0`: Minimum 10 seconds for JWT tokens\n  - `maximalJwtExpiryTime = 3600.0`: Maximum 1 hour for JWT tokens\n\nCommand-line options defined in `AuthenticationFeature::collectOptions()`:\n  - `--server.authentication`: Enable/disable authentication\n  - `--server.authentication-timeout`: Token cache timeout\n  - `--server.session-timeout`: JWT session lifetime\n  - `--auth.minimal-jwt-expiry-time`: Minimum JWT expiry\n  - `--auth.maximal-jwt-expiry-time`: Maximum JWT expiry\n  - `--server.jwt-secret`: JWT signing secret\n  - `--server.jwt-secret-keyfile`: Path to JWT key file\n  - `--server.jwt-secret-folder`: Path to JWT secret folder\n\n## Supporting Classes\n\n**`arangod/Auth/Handler.h`:**\n- `Handler` interface: Base class for custom authentication handlers\n- `HandlerResult`: Result class carrying authentication success/failure and roles\n\n**`arangod/Auth/User.h`/`cpp`:**\n- `User` class: Represents a user with:\n  - Username and password hash\n  - Active flag\n  - Database-level permissions map\n  - Collection-level permissions map\n  - Methods: `grantDatabase()`, `grantCollection()`, `databaseAuthLevel()`, `collectionAuthLevel()`\n\n**`arangod/Auth/Common.h`:**\n- `Level` enum: RW (Read-Write), RO (Read-Only), NONE (No Access), UNDEFINED\n- Authentication level constants and utilities\n\n**`arangod/RestHandler/RestAuthHandler.h`/`cpp`:**\n- `RestAuthHandler`: Implements `/_open/auth` endpoint for JWT token generation\n- Generates JWT tokens from username/password credentials\n- Respects `minimalJwtExpiryTime` and `maximalJwtExpiryTime` constraints\n\n**`arangod/GeneralServer/CommTask.cpp`:**\n- `CommTask::handleRequest()`: Main request processing that:\n  - Extracts authentication from HTTP headers\n  - Calls `TokenCache::checkAuthentication()`\n  - Sets user context in request\n  - Enforces database-level authorization\n  - Uses `ExecContext` to track permissions during request processing\n\n## Authentication Flow\n\n1. Client sends HTTP request with authentication (Basic or Bearer JWT)\n2. `CommTask::handleRequest()` extracts authentication header\n3. `TokenCache::checkAuthentication()` validates credentials:\n   - For Basic auth: Looks up user in cache or database via `UserManager`\n   - For JWT: Parses and validates JWT signature (HMAC-SHA256 or ES256)\n4. If valid, `TokenCache::Entry` is returned with username and expiry\n5. `ExecContext` is created with user's permission levels from `UserManager`\n6. Request is processed with authorization checks via `ExecContext`\n7. `RestUsersHandler` manages user account operations via `/_api/user/*` endpoints\n\n## Authorization Resolution\n\nPermission levels are resolved hierarchically:\n1. System-level: Full read-write or read-only access across all databases\n2. Database-level: Access rights to specific databases (includes wildcard \"*\" for default)\n3. Collection-level: Access rights to specific collections within databases\n\nThe `UserManager::databaseAuthLevel()` and `collectionAuthLevel()` methods perform this resolution with fallback to wildcard entries if specific permissions are not defined.\n"
}

